title: Ep. 14 - This Game is Impossible to Predict
creator: West of Everest: An Oklahoma Football Podcast
subject: Podcast
description: Grant relives his history with the OU-Texas game, then Lee joins in to take a victory lap because he was 100 percent correct about Jordan Thomas's play against Iowa State. After that the guys say which injured player they hope plays for OU, discuss what will happen on Saturday, and finally unveil the updated Top 10 plus Week 7 picks.6:30 Grant explains in detail why he absolutely loves the DeMarco Murray long TD run against Texas in 20078:40 why OU-Texas is so unique and one of a kind10:10 Lincoln Riley says no defensive coaching changes are on the table11:00 On Monday, Riley confirmed pretty much everything Lee said about Jordan Thomas last week. So Lee takes a victory lap.15:00 injury updates with the help of CeeDee Lamb on Twitter17:35 Lee looks back on how the Texas defense attacked OU's offense in last year's game22:55 Grant has an incredibly offensive way at describing how he felt about the Sooners offense last year against Texas24:30 If you could pick one injured Sooner to be 100 percent healthy and active this weekend, who would it be?31:10 The Horns defense is susceptible to big plays33:15 Lee's worried that the Texas defensive pressure could lead to OU making stupid mistakes34:05 Grant goes over what the Texas defense looked like on tape last week against Kansas State37:20 Grant talks about how much the Texas offense has improved since the USC game in Week 339:35 Grant randomly goes on about Kansas State's defense for some reason.40:30 will Texas just try and throw the ball all around the yard and pick on JT this Saturday?42:50 There's reason for hope in regards to OU's defense by looking back at the Ohio State game44:20 What do you *want* to see happen in OU-Texas?47:40 What *will* happen Saturday?50:20 Lee is deeply sorry for not providing a score prediction. This game is impossible to predict given the circumstances.50:40 Grant points out how weird it is that OU played so well against Ohio State and then so poorly against Iowa State51:40 the guys each countdown their latest Top 10 rankings52:20 Grant welcomes Washington State and Wisconsin into his Top 1053:50 Lee continues to rank OU in his Top 10 and we discuss what would happen if the Sooners played Wisconsin56:10 Grant bumps Miami up to No. 8 in his poll this week57:20 Lee moves TCU up to No. 7 and he's still not sold on the Frogs58:05 Lee clarifies what he means by Penn State being a \"fraud\"1:01:10 Washington is taking care of business despite playing a soft schedule1:02:20 we both have Georgia at No. 4 and Grant is concerned about the 'Dogs one dimensional offense1:03:00 Grant is beginning to hedge his bet on Penn State being a fraud1:04:25 Lee bumps Ohio State up to No. 31:05:25 Grant still says \"Pump the brakes\" on Clemson's offense1:07:30 Week 7 PicksTexas Tech-West VirginiaAuburn-LSUGeorgia Tech-MiamiUtah-USCOregon-Stanford#westofeverest #oufootball #oklahoma #oklahomafootball #sooners #soonersfootball #jordanthomas #universityofoklahoma #lincolnriley #bakermayfield #redriverrivalry #redriver #redrivershootout #outexas
